instruction:
Let $f {\in} L ( [ 0, \infty) ), a > 0$. What is the value of $\int_{0}^{+\infty} \sin(ax) \, \mathrm{d}x \int_{0}^{+\infty} f(y) \mathrm{e}^{-xy} \, \mathrm{d}y$?

Options:
A. $$
\int_{0}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {y^{2}+a^{2}}
$$
B. $$
2a \! \int_{0}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {a^{2}+y^{3}}
$$
C. $$
a \! \int_{0}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {a^{2}+y^{2}}
$$
D. $$
a \! \int_{0}^{1} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {a^{2}+y^{2}}
$$
E. $$
a^{2} \! \int_{0}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {1+a^{2}}
$$
F. $$
a \! \int_{0}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {1+y^{2}}
$$
G. $$
\frac{a}{2} \! \int_{0}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {y^{2}+x}
$$
H. $$
a^{3} \! \int_{0}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {a^{2}+y}
$$
I. $$
\int_{0}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {x^{2}+a}
$$
J. $$
a \! \int_{1}^{+\infty} \frac{f ( y ) \mathrm{d} y} {a^{3}+y^{2}}
$$
